texts.textentryhtml: Offered by artist's sons to the United States in 1826; sold by them (Robins, London, May 22-25, 1829, lot 79); bought by Richard Cooke (RA, 1784-1857); Vose Galleries, Boston, MA; John F. Braun, Merion, PA, by 1921; purchased by Museum from John Levy Galleries, New York, NY
